  "texts": [
    "In the limit of few deflecting masses, the time delay is largely unperturbed, as shown in Fig. 5.",
    "There are scattered logarithmic spikes, but the likelihood of one lying close to the line-of-sight to the source is low.",
    "The locations of the microimages satisfy the lens equation, which we re-write here as:",
    "where α B (θ) and α * (θ) are the deflection angles due to the potential ψ B and the microlenses (with the negative constant convergence correction) respectively.",
    "For constant second derivatives of the potential ψ B (constant κ and γ), the first two terms of the lens equation become proportional to θ."
